```C# Snippet:CreateConsumptionBudget
```

### List budgets

```C# Snippet:ListConsumptionBudgets
```

### List usage details

```C# Snippet:ListConsumptionUsageDetails
```
```

---

### Step 3: Verify README structure

The README currently contains all required top-level sections. The following sections need improvement:

| Section | Status | Action needed |
|---|---|---|
| Getting started | ✅ Present | No change |
| Key concepts | ⚠️ Generic only | Replace with service-specific description of scope model and main resource types |
| Examples | ❌ No inline code | Add snippet placeholders (see Step 2) |
| Troubleshooting | ✅ Present | No change |
| Next steps | ✅ Present | No change |
| Contributing | ✅ Present | No change |

Use `sdk/keyvault/Azure.Security.KeyVault.Secrets/README.md` as the canonical reference for section formatting and tone.

---

### Step 4: Validate

Run these commands in order:

1. `dotnet build sdk/consumption/Azure.ResourceManager.Consumption/`
2. `dotnet test sdk/consumption/Azure.ResourceManager.Consumption/ --filter TestCategory!=Live`
3. `eng/scripts/Update-Snippets.ps1 consumption` — injects snippet code from test `#region` tags into README placeholders; verify the diff shows the snippets populated
4. `eng/scripts/Export-API.ps1 consumption` — regenerates public API listing files (no public API was changed in this push, but run as a precaution)
5. `dotnet format sdk/consumption/Azure.ResourceManager.Consumption/`

</details>

